---
import Section from './Section.astro'
import { runData, fmtOffset } from '../lib/run'

// The real sentry moment from the bundled run (kind: overlap), if recorded.
const overlap = runData.events.find((e) => e.kind === 'overlap')
---

<Section id="coordination" title="prevented, not advised">
  <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-pretty text-lp-muted">
      <p>
        real-time advice isn't enough — an LLM can ignore it. so before a worker reads a file it
        must <span class="font-mono text-lp-fg">claim</span> it. if a teammate owns it, the read is
        blocked at the tool boundary and the worker is redirected to the existing finding.
      </p>
      <p>
        deterministic, not persuasive: on a live 3-worker run this prevented
        <b class="font-mono text-lp-fg">4 duplicate reads</b> before they happened — redundant
        reads hit 0. the same gate, turned around, guards Write in build mode:
        claim-on-write means <b class="font-mono text-lp-fg">no clobbers</b> (claim ON:
        prevented-clobbers=1, collisions=0 · claim OFF: collisions=1).
      </p>
      <p>
        around every task, the society works the brain: the Planner builds a dependency graph, the
        Conductor pulls and pushes knowledge, the Sentry flags overlap live, and the Critic rejects
        weak answers so a cut-off worker can't poison the memory.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure class="overflow-hidden rounded-md border border-lp-border bg-lp-surface">
      <div class="border-b border-lp-border px-4 py-2 font-mono text-xs text-lp-muted">
        the sentry, live — from the run recorded on this page
      </div>
      <div class="px-4 py-4 font-mono text-xs leading-6">
        {overlap ? (
          <>
            <div class="text-lp-muted">{fmtOffset(overlap.t)} · {overlap.actor}</div>
            <div class="mt-1 text-lp-accent">{overlap.text}</div>
            <div class="mt-3 text-lp-muted">
              two workers converged on the claim registry — flagged the moment it happened, not in
              a post-mortem.
            </div>
          </>
        ) : (
          <div class="text-lp-muted">no overlap occurred in the bundled run — the assignment kept every file disjoint.</div>
        )}
      </div>
    </figure>
  </div>
</Section>
